instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "Enrichment – Building Control Engineers model devices, actuators and control logic directly within BIM, producing enriched BIM models that capture building component‑system (BCS) elements. Extraction – Using model‑driven engineering (MDE) principles, the framework automatically extracts structured, semantic representations from the enriched BIM (e.g., GIS‑compatible data structures). Deployment – The extracted models are compiled into deployable Digital Twin artifacts (containers, microservices) with minimal manual intervention; DT Engineers deploy these artifacts to a runtime environment. Operation – Real‑time data‑exchange protocols (e.g., MQTT or OPC UA) continuously sync sensor/actuator streams between the physical building and the DT, enabling Facility Managers to monitor status and issue control commands via interactive visualization dashboards. Extension – Custom services, analytics and plugins are added through standardized extension points, leveraging a modular architecture that isolates new functionality while preserving core runtime integrity. Maintenance – Lifecycle governance relies on automated transformation pipelines and versioned BIM artifacts; manual intervention is limited to configuration changes, and incremental updates to BIM models trigger regeneration of the Corresponding DT artifacts, ensuring consistency across lifecycle stages."
]

